The paper proposes a method for automatically generating a network architecture for semantic image segmentation, which is a task in computer vision (cs.CV). The approach involves exploring the search space for an optimized computation cell, which suggests a machine learning approach (cs.LG). The paper also discusses assigning costs to operations to optimize the architecture under constraints, which involves optimization and potentially reinforcement learning (cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the approach on image datasets, which suggests a focus on computer vision and potentially natural language processing (cs.CL).
